    en: "New York's Real Property Tax Credit is a refundable income tax credit for low-income households that pay rent or property tax on their home. NY Tax Law § 606(e) authorizes the credit. Households with income under $18,000 can claim the credit on Form IT-214 — even if they owe no income tax. Renters claim a portion of their rent as 'real property taxes paid through rent.' Homeowners claim actual property tax. The maximum credit is $375 per qualifying household. The credit is often missed by low-income filers who do not file an income tax return at all because they have no tax owed."
